228
00:07:46,604 --> 00:07:48,603
- without complaining or refusing. - Yes.

229
00:07:48,604 --> 00:07:50,104
But Jang Hoon was different.

230
00:07:50,974 --> 00:07:52,044
How so?

231
00:07:52,404 --> 00:07:54,173
- He didn't follow the directions? - Jang Hoon was like...

232
00:07:54,174 --> 00:07:55,174
Yes?

233
00:07:55,774 --> 00:07:59,143
"It's not that I won't do as you said."

234
00:07:59,144 --> 00:08:00,784
"I am willing to do my best."

235
00:08:01,444 --> 00:08:03,683
(Jang Hoon is always the same in any situations.)

236
00:08:03,684 --> 00:08:04,913
"But don't you think..."

237
00:08:04,914 --> 00:08:07,783
- He's rebellious. - "we should do it this way?"

238
00:08:07,784 --> 00:08:10,123
He didn't hesitate to speak up and express his opinions.

239
00:08:10,124 --> 00:08:11,494
But while complaining,

240
00:08:12,194 --> 00:08:14,994
he completed what he was told to do perfectly.

241
00:08:15,464 --> 00:08:16,963
- Cheon Mu is impressive. - I saw that...

242
00:08:16,964 --> 00:08:18,593
He complains, but he does what he has to do.

243
00:08:18,594 --> 00:08:20,264
I saw that and found him to be so great.

244
00:08:20,604 --> 00:08:22,774
I told myself to always speak my mind...

245
00:08:23,374 --> 00:08:25,103
when I grew up just as Jang Hoon did.

246
00:08:25,104 --> 00:08:26,403
- No. - Cheon Mu.

247
00:08:26,404 --> 00:08:27,803
- He said no. - When you shot the commercial,

248
00:08:27,804 --> 00:08:29,744
Jang Hoon gave you some pocket money, right?

249
00:08:30,214 --> 00:08:31,644
Well... He didn't.

250
00:08:32,544 --> 00:08:33,544
- You see... - Oh, dear.

251
00:08:33,545 --> 00:08:34,713
(Oh, he didn't.)

252
00:08:34,714 --> 00:08:37,353
- We all thought he did. - Look at Ji Woo.

253
00:08:37,354 --> 00:08:38,383
- You know... - Ji Woo,

254
00:08:38,384 --> 00:08:39,824
should he have given Cheon Mu some pocket money or not?

255
00:08:40,484 --> 00:08:41,924
- He should have. - Right.

256
00:08:42,624 --> 00:08:44,493
- You know, I... - He said Jang Hoon should have.

257
00:08:44,494 --> 00:08:45,824
Anyway...

258
00:08:46,194 --> 00:08:48,323
I feel very honored...

259
00:08:48,324 --> 00:08:51,393
to have worked with such a top star.

260
00:08:51,394 --> 00:08:55,404
I'm honored to have shot a TV commercial with you.

261
00:08:55,634 --> 00:08:58,034
Does any of you know me?

262
00:08:58,304 --> 00:08:59,643
- I do. - She knows Sang Min?

263
00:08:59,644 --> 00:09:02,714
- As a member of Roo'Ra? - I know a lot about Sang Min.

264
00:09:02,944 --> 00:09:05,484
My grandma used to be a fan of Roo'Ra.

265
00:09:07,014 --> 00:09:08,184
- Her grandma was a fan. - So...

266
00:09:08,284 --> 00:09:10,584
I thought you were saying your grandmother had lent him money.

267
00:09:11,914 --> 00:09:15,283
- So I heard of him many times. - How old is your grandmother?

268
00:09:15,284 --> 00:09:16,793
Su Yeon, I'm pretty sure that...

269
00:09:16,794 --> 00:09:19,494
your grandmother is around Sang Min's age.

270
00:09:20,824 --> 00:09:23,063
- How old is your grandmother? - How old is your grandmother?

271
00:09:23,064 --> 00:09:24,233
She's in her late 50s.

272
00:09:24,234 --> 00:09:26,063
- Then she's around Ho Dong's age. - Oh, I see.

273
00:09:26,064 --> 00:09:27,864
- So your grandmother... - Her grandmother is...

274
00:09:28,064 --> 00:09:31,133
- around Ho Dong's age. - was a fan of Roo'Ra?

275
00:09:31,134 --> 00:09:32,243
That makes sense.

276
00:09:32,244 --> 00:09:35,173
I know we're all friends. But didn't you bring anything?

277
00:09:35,174 --> 00:09:37,674
You should bring something to transfer to our school.

278
00:09:37,874 --> 00:09:39,714
- We left it to the youngest one. - It's the youngest one's job.

279
00:09:39,984 --> 00:09:42,153
Before that, play the music now.

280
00:09:42,154 --> 00:09:43,784
- What? - What is he going to do?

281
00:09:43,914 --> 00:09:45,183
- What are you doing? - Be careful.

282
00:09:45,184 --> 00:09:46,583
- Be careful. - What is he doing?

283
00:09:46,584 --> 00:09:47,783
- What is he going to do? - Slickback dance?

284
00:09:47,784 --> 00:09:49,994
- Min Ho, help him. - I know this song.

285
00:09:50,224 --> 00:09:52,024
- Isn't it the slickback dance song? - You can bring the whole backpack.

286
00:09:52,494 --> 00:09:53,763
- Be careful. - Why?

287
00:09:53,764 --> 00:09:54,894
Okay.

288
00:09:55,434 --> 00:09:56,494
He's good at it.

289
00:09:56,794 --> 00:09:58,193
(The trot prodigy dances the slickback.)

290
00:09:58,194 --> 00:10:00,304
- He's good at it. - He's so cute.

291
00:10:00,464 --> 00:10:01,704
- He's good at it. - He's so cute.

292
00:10:01,964 --> 00:10:04,574
(He runs toward Soo Geun, floating in the air.)

293
00:10:06,304 --> 00:10:07,644
(Smiling)

294
00:10:08,914 --> 00:10:10,373
- Ji Woo is so good at that. - Do the dance again.

295
00:10:10,374 --> 00:10:12,384
- Great job! - Do it on your way back.

296
00:10:13,244 --> 00:10:15,714
(Goodbye, everyone.)

297
00:10:15,954 --> 00:10:17,654
- Way to go! Keep going! - He's good at it.

298
00:10:17,754 --> 00:10:19,254
- Way to go! Keep going! - Impressive.

299
00:10:19,324 --> 00:10:20,383
He's good at it.

300
00:10:20,384 --> 00:10:21,683
- Ji Woo. - I'm impressed.

301
00:10:21,684 --> 00:10:22,753
Ji Woo, come back here.

302
00:10:22,754 --> 00:10:24,123
Teach me how to do that.

303
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:26,063
- He jumps so lightly. - How do you do that?

304
00:10:26,064 --> 00:10:27,123
Walk me through it...

305
00:10:27,124 --> 00:10:28,664
Walk me through it, step by step.

306
00:10:28,864 --> 00:10:31,194
- First, lift up your right foot. - Yes.

307
00:10:31,294 --> 00:10:32,933
Then slide it to your right side...

308
00:10:32,934 --> 00:10:34,734
- and put it down on the floor. - Okay.

309
00:10:34,864 --> 00:10:37,003
Next, lift up your left foot.

310
00:10:37,004 --> 00:10:38,844
- You should try it too. - Put it down. Do all steps fast.

311
00:10:42,414 --> 00:10:43,544
- He's really good at it. - I'm amazed.

312
00:10:43,744 --> 00:10:45,244
- That's no joke. - Great job.

313
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:46,484
How does he do that?

314
00:10:47,184 --> 00:10:49,683
- Cheon Mu, can you do it too? - Me?

315
00:10:49,684 --> 00:10:51,653
- It's okay if you can't. - Dance!

316
00:10:51,654 --> 00:10:53,623
- Give it a try. He can do it too. - Dance!

317
00:10:53,624 --> 00:10:55,383
- He seems confident. - Cheon Mu.

318
00:10:55,384 --> 00:10:56,654
Play the music.

319
00:10:57,994 --> 00:10:59,064
This isn't how it looked.

320
00:11:00,424 --> 00:11:01,494
This isn't how it looked.

321
00:11:04,234 --> 00:11:05,334
This isn't how it looked.

322
00:11:08,604 --> 00:11:10,403
It's okay to say you can't do it.

323
00:11:10,404 --> 00:11:12,503
- Try it again. - That's the Bongsan mask dance.

324
00:11:12,504 --> 00:11:14,703
(Dancing awkwardly)

325
00:11:14,704 --> 00:11:16,473
- Can't you do it? - You can't do it, can you?

326
00:11:16,474 --> 00:11:17,573
(He feels a surge of embarrassment.)

327
00:11:17,574 --> 00:11:18,773
- Cheon Mu. - I see how good he's at it now.

328
00:11:18,774 --> 00:11:20,043
- Cheon Mu... - He's good at it.

329
00:11:20,044 --> 00:11:22,213
- You need to move lightly. - I just saw Jang Hoon in you.

330
00:11:22,214 --> 00:11:24,153
"It's not that I won't do it."

331
00:11:24,154 --> 00:11:26,583
("It's not that I won't do it.")

332
00:11:26,584 --> 00:11:28,183
Because they shot a commercial together,

333
00:11:28,184 --> 00:11:30,993
- they're alike. - You don't have to be good at it.

334
00:11:30,994 --> 00:11:32,523
Gwan Sik is so adorable.

335
00:11:32,524 --> 00:11:34,693
- The transfer form. - Hi, Gwan Sik.

336
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,763
Park Sung On, Kim Tae Yeon, Hwang Min Ho, Lee Cheon Mu,

337
00:11:36,764 --> 00:11:38,694
Lee Su Yeon, Oh Ji Yul, and Ryu Ji Woo.

338
00:11:40,164 --> 00:11:44,273
The seven of them wrote what they wanted to become...

339
00:11:44,274 --> 00:11:45,943
when they grew up.

340
00:11:45,944 --> 00:11:47,174
- Okay. - First up is Sung On.

341
00:11:47,674 --> 00:11:49,244
Sung On, did you really write this?

342
00:11:49,474 --> 00:11:51,443
You wrote you wanted to become a Buddhist monk.

343
00:11:51,444 --> 00:11:54,084
- What? - It's not that I want to.

344
00:11:54,314 --> 00:11:57,783
But I think I will most likely become one.

345
00:11:57,784 --> 00:11:59,153
- Why? - I'm not greedy...

346
00:11:59,154 --> 00:12:00,683
about materialistic things at all.

347
00:12:00,684 --> 00:12:02,223
There's nothing I want to have.

348
00:12:02,224 --> 00:12:04,493
Normally, kids at my age want something,

349
00:12:04,494 --> 00:12:06,464
- at least one. - Yes.

350
00:12:06,864 --> 00:12:09,064
- But I don't want anything. - Really?

351
00:12:09,364 --> 00:12:10,493
So I don't have many things either.

352
00:12:10,494 --> 00:12:13,133
- Then do you give your parents... - We all want something.

353
00:12:13,134 --> 00:12:14,834
all the money that you earn?

354
00:12:15,004 --> 00:12:17,133
I save half in my bank account.

355
00:12:17,134 --> 00:12:18,833
I give the rest to my grandparents as pocket money...

356
00:12:18,834 --> 00:12:21,203
- on national holidays like Chuseok. - But you said you weren't greedy.

357
00:12:21,204 --> 00:12:24,373
I also donate some to ChildFund Korea.

358
00:12:24,374 --> 00:12:25,644
He's just like Ho Dong.

359
00:12:26,114 --> 00:12:27,883
- Ho Dong donates a lot as well. - Oh, I see.

360
00:12:27,884 --> 00:12:29,384
And when I receive some snacks,

361
00:12:29,714 --> 00:12:32,113
- I can't eat them as I'm on a diet. - Really?

362
00:12:32,114 --> 00:12:34,884
So I donate the snacks to those who need them.

363
00:12:35,054 --> 00:12:37,454
You don't seem materialistic, but you do seem gluttonous.

364
00:12:37,994 --> 00:12:40,164
- When it comes to food... - How could you say it to a child?

365
00:12:40,324 --> 00:12:43,333
- It's the Children's Day special! - I can explain.

366
00:12:43,334 --> 00:12:45,163
- Does that even matter? - Apologize to him.

367
00:12:45,164 --> 00:12:46,963
- That was mean, to be honest. - How could you say it to a child?

368
00:12:46,964 --> 00:12:49,103
- I was trying to say... - We should eat on Children's Day.

369
00:12:49,104 --> 00:12:50,104
That's right.

370
00:12:50,105 --> 00:12:53,373
I mean, you're not totally disinterested in food, right?

371
00:12:53,374 --> 00:12:55,443
- Right. I have a good appetite. - Kids at his age eat a lot.

372
00:12:55,444 --> 00:12:56,773
But I've been on a diet.

373
00:12:56,774 --> 00:12:58,373
You said you didn't even eat snacks.

374
00:12:58,374 --> 00:13:00,244
Of course. I didn't have much for a meal earlier.

375
00:13:00,584 --> 00:13:02,413
- He ate snacks in the green room. - I'm trying to lose weight.

376
00:13:02,414 --> 00:13:03,614
In the green room?

377
00:13:03,754 --> 00:13:05,084
- I saw him eating cookies... - I guess he can't help it.

378
00:13:05,184 --> 00:13:07,754
- In the green room... - Why did you lie, Sung On?

379
00:13:09,054 --> 00:13:10,824
You shouldn't lie on a TV show.

380
00:13:11,294 --> 00:13:13,663
- I saw you eating a lot of cookies. - No, I didn't eat any.

381
00:13:13,664 --> 00:13:16,034
- You were enjoying them... - Here's why I'm on a diet.

382
00:13:16,364 --> 00:13:18,894
When I was competing on "Mister Trot 2,"

383
00:13:19,104 --> 00:13:21,064
I spent so much energy on dancing.

384
00:13:21,804 --> 00:13:24,734
- And that caused hyperventilation. - I see.

385
00:13:24,934 --> 00:13:27,343
I went to see a doctor...

386
00:13:27,344 --> 00:13:30,314
and asked if I could get an IV and rest.

387
00:13:30,614 --> 00:13:34,283
And the doctor said that I had enough nutrients in my body,

388
00:13:34,284 --> 00:13:35,814
so I didn't need an IV.

389
00:13:36,984 --> 00:13:38,553
- He's just like Ho Dong. - The doctor...

390
00:13:38,554 --> 00:13:41,724
- We should call him Park Ho Dong. - My mom practically begged him...

391
00:13:41,854 --> 00:13:43,753
- to give me an IV. - Yes.

392
00:13:43,754 --> 00:13:44,993
But the doctor refused, saying I had...

393
00:13:44,994 --> 00:13:46,223
- too much nutrients in my body. - You had too much?

394
00:13:46,224 --> 00:13:48,424
- It shouldn't be too much. - I was shocked.

395
00:13:48,594 --> 00:13:49,963
- I've never heard such a case. - I was so shocked.

396
00:13:49,964 --> 00:13:51,294
I have overnutrition, apparently.

397
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:53,903
- Overnutrition? - Park Ho Dong.

398
00:13:53,904 --> 00:13:56,304
- Not undernutrition. - He must've eaten so well.

399
00:13:56,374 --> 00:13:57,874
- I've never heard of overnutrition. - Exactly.

400
00:13:58,134 --> 00:14:00,374
- Next up is Tae Yeon. - We did it back then...

401
00:14:00,504 --> 00:14:04,074
Tae Yeon wrote two things...

402
00:14:04,214 --> 00:14:06,113
which are "chef" and "farmer."

403
00:14:06,114 --> 00:14:07,183
- Yes. - A farmer?

404
00:14:07,184 --> 00:14:09,014
- You want to become a farmer? - A farmer?

405
00:14:09,684 --> 00:14:13,224
I want to become a chef because I like eating food so much.

406
00:14:13,384 --> 00:14:16,124
I want to cook for myself and enjoy the food I made.

407
00:14:16,294 --> 00:14:18,923
As for a farmer, in "When Life Gives You Tangerines,"

408
00:14:18,924 --> 00:14:20,463
- I grow cabbage. - That's right.

409
00:14:20,464 --> 00:14:21,864
(In "When Life Gives You Tangerines," I grow cabbage.)

410
00:14:22,494 --> 00:14:27,163
(Ae Soon cultivates a stone field and grows cabbage in the drama.)

411
00:14:27,164 --> 00:14:28,203
That's right.

412
00:14:28,204 --> 00:14:31,704
I tried a farming work on set, and I found it so fun.

413
00:14:31,974 --> 00:14:35,273
And that made me want to grow crops myself...

414
00:14:35,274 --> 00:14:37,114
in my own field.

415
00:14:37,874 --> 00:14:40,243
What dish are you best at making?

416
00:14:40,244 --> 00:14:42,713
I haven't cooked many times, though.

417
00:14:42,714 --> 00:14:46,023
I've made steamed eggs and braised chicken.

418
00:14:46,024 --> 00:14:47,824
- Braised chicken? - You know how to make those?

419
00:14:47,984 --> 00:14:49,794
- I'm sure Ae Soon knows. - Right.

420
00:14:50,424 --> 00:14:51,924
Ae Soon knows how to make all kinds of dishes.

421
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:53,724
She can make any dishes.

422
00:14:53,824 --> 00:14:55,623
Next up is Cheon Mu.

423
00:14:55,624 --> 00:14:57,194
"Yes! Goal!"

424
00:14:57,594 --> 00:14:59,703
He dreams of becoming a soccer commentator.

425
00:14:59,704 --> 00:15:00,763
- Do you like soccer? - Oh, I see.

426
00:15:00,764 --> 00:15:03,404
Yes, I like soccer very much.

427
00:15:03,674 --> 00:15:06,504
- I once considered a soccer player. - I see.

428
00:15:07,374 --> 00:15:11,213
But maybe because I have weak bones, every time I played soccer,

429
00:15:11,214 --> 00:15:13,744
- I got injured. - Then you shouldn't do it.

430
00:15:14,214 --> 00:15:15,684
So I gave up.

431
00:15:16,054 --> 00:15:17,853
- Not because you're not good at it? - That's right.

432
00:15:17,854 --> 00:15:20,884
- But because you have weak bones? - I'm not saying I'm good at soccer.

433
00:15:21,224 --> 00:15:24,854
Now I want to become a commentator so I can talk a lot about soccer.

434
00:15:25,054 --> 00:15:28,063
- Show us. - Can you show us how to do it?

435
00:15:28,064 --> 00:15:29,593
Imagine one of the teams scored a goal.

436
00:15:29,594 --> 00:15:31,393
"Korea lost an opponent. And he shoots!"

437
00:15:31,394 --> 00:15:32,833
"Son Heung Min scored a goal!" Say these lines.

438
00:15:32,834 --> 00:15:33,933
"Son Heung Min..."

439
00:15:33,934 --> 00:15:35,304
"All right. Son Heung Min..."

440
00:15:35,564 --> 00:15:37,134
"just lost an opponent."

441
00:15:37,674 --> 00:15:39,604
"Goal! He scored a goal!"

442
00:15:40,904 --> 00:15:42,303
(The little Shin Moon Sun knows what to say and how to say it.)

443
00:15:42,304 --> 00:15:43,414
That was neat.

444
00:15:43,844 --> 00:15:45,243
He acted passionately. That was great.

445
00:15:45,244 --> 00:15:48,414
Next up is Ji Yul. She wrote... Oh, my.

446
00:15:48,784 --> 00:15:50,213
This is incredible.

447
00:15:50,214 --> 00:15:51,383
- How will she do all these? - I want to become many things.

448
00:15:51,384 --> 00:15:52,584
Ji Yul wrote a lot of things.

449
00:15:53,024 --> 00:15:55,384
Songwriter, idol singer, voice actress,

450
00:15:55,584 --> 00:15:57,894
emoji designer, and sommelier.

451
00:15:58,724 --> 00:16:02,324
- Sommelier? - Do you know what a sommelier is?

452
00:16:02,734 --> 00:16:04,993
Of course, I know. I want to become one.

453
00:16:04,994 --> 00:16:06,704
Why wouldn't I know what it is?

454
00:16:07,834 --> 00:16:09,203
Exactly. She dreams of becoming one.

455
00:16:09,204 --> 00:16:10,903
(Jang Hoon is lost for words as she said the right thing.)

456
00:16:10,904 --> 00:16:12,333
- She's absolutely right. - Sorry.

457
00:16:12,334 --> 00:16:14,504
- I'm sorry. - She's right.

458
00:16:14,774 --> 00:16:16,073
- I'm sorry. - She wrote her dream.

459
00:16:16,074 --> 00:16:17,414
Then why would she not know what it is?

460
00:16:17,744 --> 00:16:18,943
Well, Ji Yul...

461
00:16:18,944 --> 00:16:20,683
- Ji Yul. - You won't apologize, will you?

462
00:16:20,684 --> 00:16:24,213
- I'm sorry. I didn't know. - In my school,

463
00:16:24,214 --> 00:16:26,124
there are several water stations.

464
00:16:26,284 --> 00:16:28,884
There are about two of them on each floor.

465
00:16:29,084 --> 00:16:32,624
I numbered the taps starting from the right end.

466
00:16:32,794 --> 00:16:35,023
I tasted the water from each of the taps...

467
00:16:35,024 --> 00:16:36,033
- and wrote a memo. - Are you that serious?

468
00:16:36,034 --> 00:16:38,564
I tasted the water from all taps and wrote how it tasted.

469
00:16:38,734 --> 00:16:40,733
- You tasted the water? - That's amazing.

470
00:16:40,734 --> 00:16:42,133
Kids didn't even know the term "water station" back in my day.

471
00:16:42,134 --> 00:16:43,534
- Whenever I want to drink water, - We used to call it just a tap.

472
00:16:43,774 --> 00:16:48,043
I choose a specific tap to have more delicious water.

473
00:16:48,044 --> 00:16:50,414
- You taste water from all taps? - Can you describe delicious water?

474
00:16:51,044 --> 00:16:55,143
Although water with minerals is good for health,

475
00:16:55,144 --> 00:16:57,653
I don't really like it because it has a slimy texture.

476
00:16:57,654 --> 00:16:58,913
(Yul-melier has a high-end preference.)

477
00:16:58,914 --> 00:17:00,054
- That's accurate. - Slimy?

478
00:17:00,324 --> 00:17:02,184
- That's an accurate analysis. - Tap water in school has minerals?

479
00:17:02,454 --> 00:17:04,324
- I like mineral water. - Minerals?

480
00:17:04,494 --> 00:17:08,093
But I haven't decided what I'm going to specialize in.

481
00:17:08,094 --> 00:17:10,563
I could be a water expert. I could be a sommelier.

482
00:17:10,564 --> 00:17:13,133
I could be a food expert. I haven't decided yet.

483
00:17:13,134 --> 00:17:15,834
- You're considering many things. - You can decide when you grow up.

484
00:17:16,374 --> 00:17:18,674
- Next up is Su Yeon. Impressive. - Su Yeon, the TV show host.

485
00:17:18,904 --> 00:17:20,674
- You must be busy. - She's a good host.

486
00:17:21,144 --> 00:17:23,043
You should study hard too.

487
00:17:23,044 --> 00:17:24,943
She wrote she wanted to become an actress and a doctor.

