He said he was shocked...

738
00:27:19,674 --> 00:27:21,543
to see Ji Woo sing,

739
00:27:21,544 --> 00:27:23,644
- Ji Woo. - so why don't we give it a try?

740
00:27:24,144 --> 00:27:25,473
- Let's clap for him. - Come on.

741
00:27:25,474 --> 00:27:27,513
Ji Woo.

742
00:27:27,514 --> 00:27:29,544
(Let's all clap for him.)

743
00:27:30,154 --> 00:27:32,054
- Look at him. - He prepared something.

744
00:27:32,354 --> 00:27:33,354
Let's go, Ji Woo.

745
00:27:33,355 --> 00:27:35,424
What will you be singing, Ji Woo?

746
00:27:36,124 --> 00:27:38,693
- I will sing "Don't You Know," - "Don't You Know."

747
00:27:38,694 --> 00:27:40,723
- by ZO ZAZZ. - Gosh.

748
00:27:40,724 --> 00:27:42,993
You're going to sing "Don't You Know?"

749
00:27:42,994 --> 00:27:44,463
- That's a hard song. - Amazing.

750
00:27:44,464 --> 00:27:45,534
Please give me the music.

751
00:27:45,894 --> 00:27:47,163
"Please give me the music."

752
00:27:47,164 --> 00:27:49,874
He learned to speak so beautifully.

753
00:27:50,674 --> 00:27:54,274
("Don't You Know" by ZO ZAZZ)

754
00:27:55,104 --> 00:27:58,444
(Will the 9-year-old be able to express lonely longing?)

755
00:28:51,034 --> 00:28:56,903
(You give no answer at all)

756
00:28:56,904 --> 00:28:58,434
- That's amazing. - That's amazing.

757
00:29:06,744 --> 00:29:13,014
(I wait, no matter the season)

758
00:29:15,154 --> 00:29:16,254
How does he...

759
00:29:21,924 --> 00:29:27,034
(The sorrow of a 9-year-old musical prodigy)

760
00:29:30,274 --> 00:29:32,673
(Don't you...)

761
00:29:32,674 --> 00:29:35,303
(Know)

762
00:29:35,304 --> 00:29:36,814
- Gosh. - He's amazing.

763
00:29:37,114 --> 00:29:39,173
- Seriously. - That's shocking.

764
00:29:39,174 --> 00:29:41,313
- Gosh, Ji Woo. - Goodness.

765
00:29:41,314 --> 00:29:43,583
- Ji Woo. - You're amazing.

766
00:29:43,584 --> 00:29:45,213
- Can I have your autograph? - Ji Woo, you're the best.

767
00:29:45,214 --> 00:29:46,214
That was amazing.

768
00:29:46,684 --> 00:29:49,454
(What is love, really?)

769
00:29:49,724 --> 00:29:51,494
- Don't you know? - Ji Woo.

770
00:29:51,754 --> 00:29:54,294
Do you know what the lyrics are about?

771
00:29:54,764 --> 00:29:55,764
I don't really know.

772
00:29:56,934 --> 00:29:57,993
You're so good.

773
00:29:57,994 --> 00:29:59,893
- He doesn't know what it's about. - He doesn't know.

774
00:29:59,894 --> 00:30:02,503
It's amazing that he's nine,

775
00:30:02,504 --> 00:30:05,733
but you can feel the emotions...

776
00:30:05,734 --> 00:30:08,743
- Yes, he has the emotions. - of a man in his 40's.

777
00:30:08,744 --> 00:30:09,773
He's so good.

778
00:30:09,774 --> 00:30:12,243
It's strange that you can feel it in his voice.

779
00:30:12,244 --> 00:30:14,043
He's actually not nine.

780
00:30:14,044 --> 00:30:15,313
He lied about his age,

781
00:30:15,314 --> 00:30:17,383
- How old is he? - but he's actually about 46.

782
00:30:17,384 --> 00:30:18,983
- Really? - Is he 46?

783
00:30:18,984 --> 00:30:20,883
- He doesn't know about it. - He's in his 40's.

784
00:30:20,884 --> 00:30:21,953
Ji Woo is shocked.

785
00:30:21,954 --> 00:30:22,954
He's almost 50.

786
00:30:22,955 --> 00:30:25,194
Ji Woo, are you actually 46?

787
00:30:26,324 --> 00:30:27,324
What?

788
00:30:27,864 --> 00:30:28,864
What?

789
00:30:28,865 --> 00:30:30,594
(It's so fun to tease him that even the camera shakes.)

790
00:30:31,594 --> 00:30:33,833
- Is that too much? - Next.

791
00:30:33,834 --> 00:30:36,033
- He's so lovely. - The next keyword is from...

792
00:30:36,034 --> 00:30:38,803
- He sounds surprised. - Tae Yeon, Cheon Mu, and Ji Yul.

793
00:30:38,804 --> 00:30:40,904
The three actors were put together.

794
00:30:41,174 --> 00:30:44,274
Tae Yeon and Cheon Mu have "When Life Gives You Tangerines."

795
00:30:44,444 --> 00:30:46,043
- Gosh. - Amazing.

796
00:30:46,044 --> 00:30:47,813
Ji Yul has "The Glory."

797
00:30:47,814 --> 00:30:49,783
- That's what they wrote. - Amazing.

798
00:30:49,784 --> 00:30:50,913
- Me? - Ji Yul.

799
00:30:50,914 --> 00:30:52,614
I'm really curious, though.

800
00:30:52,814 --> 00:30:55,424
How many years apart are you, Tae Yeon and Cheon Mu?

801
00:30:55,684 --> 00:30:57,853
We are three years apart.

802
00:30:57,854 --> 00:30:59,193
- Really? - I'm older.

803
00:30:59,194 --> 00:31:01,623
- Are you? - Tae Yeon is three years older?

804
00:31:01,624 --> 00:31:03,833
- Yes. - In the show,

805
00:31:03,834 --> 00:31:06,033
- Cheon Mu is older, right? - One year older.

806
00:31:06,034 --> 00:31:07,163
- Yes. - Gosh.

807
00:31:07,164 --> 00:31:10,333
Tae Yeon and Cheon Mu...

808
00:31:10,334 --> 00:31:13,073
were young in the show,

809
00:31:13,074 --> 00:31:16,503
so if it weren't for the uniforms, I wouldn't have recognized them.

810
00:31:16,504 --> 00:31:19,313
How long ago was the shoot?

811
00:31:19,314 --> 00:31:22,083
- We shot the drama two years ago. - I see.

812
00:31:22,084 --> 00:31:23,413
- It was two years ago? - So now,

813
00:31:23,414 --> 00:31:25,513
my hair is much longer,

814
00:31:25,514 --> 00:31:27,653
and I grew more than 10cm.

815
00:31:27,654 --> 00:31:28,654
- Yes. - You grew 10cm?

816
00:31:28,655 --> 00:31:29,883
How tall are you now?

817
00:31:29,884 --> 00:31:31,953
I am 159cm.

818
00:31:31,954 --> 00:31:34,164
You will soon be taller than Soo Geun.

819
00:31:34,594 --> 00:31:35,663
- Soo Geun us... - You're about the same size...

820
00:31:35,664 --> 00:31:36,693
as me now.

821
00:31:36,694 --> 00:31:39,233
- You must be as tall as Soo Geun. - You still have the face,

822
00:31:39,234 --> 00:31:40,663
but I saw that...

823
00:31:40,664 --> 00:31:42,404
- your height and all that... - She's much taller.

824
00:31:42,834 --> 00:31:46,973
Ae Soon is all grown up now.

825
00:31:46,974 --> 00:31:48,603
You're much taller as well. Right, Cheon Mu?

826
00:31:48,604 --> 00:31:51,614
I grew more than 10cm as well.

827
00:31:52,014 --> 00:31:54,644
And my hair is back to normal.

828
00:31:55,544 --> 00:31:57,813
You are actually so pretty and handsome,

829
00:31:57,814 --> 00:32:00,883
but you were grubby in the show.

830
00:32:00,884 --> 00:32:03,623
- Grubby. - Back then,

831
00:32:03,624 --> 00:32:06,623
I had to wear dirt makeup all over my body.

832
00:32:06,624 --> 00:32:08,493
- Dirt makeup? - Yes.

833
00:32:08,494 --> 00:32:11,563
So when I had to eat,

834
00:32:11,564 --> 00:32:13,293
it felt a bit icky.

835
00:32:13,294 --> 00:32:14,303
Yes.

836
00:32:14,304 --> 00:32:15,803
- But I couldn't wash up. - No.

837
00:32:15,804 --> 00:32:17,503
- Since you have to shoot again. - Yes.

838
00:32:17,504 --> 00:32:20,144
I was very tanned back then,

839
00:32:20,504 --> 00:32:22,843
so my mom said no one would notice,

840
00:32:22,844 --> 00:32:24,973
and that I should just wash my hands before I ate,

841
00:32:24,974 --> 00:32:26,573
and no one noticed until the end.

842
00:32:26,574 --> 00:32:28,383
- What? - Tae Yeon just heard this now.

843
00:32:28,384 --> 00:32:30,313
- I just heard now. - Cheon Mu, I see you're clean.

844
00:32:30,314 --> 00:32:32,813
You could be the future Jang Hoon.

845
00:32:32,814 --> 00:32:34,883
- Yes. - You don't like being icky,

846
00:32:34,884 --> 00:32:37,323
but you still do whatever you're told to.

847
00:32:37,324 --> 00:32:39,953
- The future Jang Hoon. - In the show,

848
00:32:39,954 --> 00:32:43,194
- Ae Soon is mean to Gwan Sik, - Yes.

849
00:32:43,494 --> 00:32:46,263
but he still gives her yellow croakers.

850
00:32:46,264 --> 00:32:48,203
Did you understand that emotion...

851
00:32:48,204 --> 00:32:49,933
two years ago, Cheon Mu?

852
00:32:49,934 --> 00:32:52,333
To be honest, as Cheon Mu,

853
00:32:52,334 --> 00:32:53,673
I didn't understand it.

854
00:32:53,674 --> 00:32:55,443
Because even when I gave her chicken,

855
00:32:55,444 --> 00:32:57,344
she tried to hit me with a rock.

856
00:32:58,874 --> 00:33:01,043
And even when I gave her the yellow croaker,

857
00:33:01,044 --> 00:33:02,613
she was mean to me.

858
00:33:02,614 --> 00:33:04,484
So as Cheon Mu,

859
00:33:04,754 --> 00:33:07,483
- I didn't understand it. - Sure.

860
00:33:07,484 --> 00:33:09,323
- But I'm Gwan Sik, - Yes.

861
00:33:09,324 --> 00:33:10,823
so I had to be in his shoes...

862
00:33:10,824 --> 00:33:12,523
and had to live in those times,

863
00:33:12,524 --> 00:33:14,093
so I just acted it.

864
00:33:14,094 --> 00:33:15,263
- You had to live like it? - You just acted it.

865
00:33:15,264 --> 00:33:16,863
- He had to live like it. - Really?

866
00:33:16,864 --> 00:33:18,533
Cheon Mu, in your opinion,

867
00:33:18,534 --> 00:33:21,103
what is the best scene in "When Life Gives You Tangerines?"

868
00:33:21,104 --> 00:33:25,433
There's a scene where I deliver yellow croakers to Ae Soon's house.

869
00:33:25,434 --> 00:33:26,434
- Yes. - Sure.

870
00:33:26,435 --> 00:33:27,503
(Gwan Sik delivers yellow croakers...)

871
00:33:27,504 --> 00:33:29,403
(to Ae Soon's house.)

872
00:33:29,404 --> 00:33:33,484
(One is for free.)

873
00:33:33,744 --> 00:33:34,843
(Glaring)

874
00:33:34,844 --> 00:33:36,183
(There are six in your family,)

875
00:33:36,184 --> 00:33:38,614
(but you always only buy five.)

876
00:33:38,954 --> 00:33:42,383
He lies that one is for free...

877
00:33:42,384 --> 00:33:43,953
in order to take care of Ae Soon,

878
00:33:43,954 --> 00:33:46,693
and that shows Gwan Sik's personality really well,

879
00:33:46,694 --> 00:33:48,463
- so I think that's the best scene. - That's right.

880
00:33:48,464 --> 00:33:51,133
Sure, it's the best scene.

881
00:33:51,134 --> 00:33:53,663
What do you think is the best scene, Tae Yeon?

882
00:33:53,664 --> 00:33:57,073
For me, it's the scene where Mom woke me up...

883
00:33:57,074 --> 00:33:59,203
in the middle of the night to feed me abalone...

884
00:33:59,204 --> 00:34:01,304
while telling me her will.

885
00:34:01,744 --> 00:34:05,974
(Ae Soon listens to her dying mother's will.)

886
00:34:06,344 --> 00:34:08,913
(Don't say it.)

887
00:34:08,914 --> 00:34:12,454
(I won't promise you!)

888
00:34:12,684 --> 00:34:15,983
I think I will be really sad if my mom woke me up...

889
00:34:15,984 --> 00:34:17,653
and told me that she was dying.

890
00:34:17,654 --> 00:34:20,863
You said you wouldn't eat it while you were crying.

891
00:34:20,864 --> 00:34:22,023
Yes, that's right.

892
00:34:22,024 --> 00:34:24,793
When you two were auditioning,

893
00:34:24,794 --> 00:34:27,263
did you know whose younger part you were playing...

894
00:34:27,264 --> 00:34:28,333
or not?

895
00:34:28,334 --> 00:34:30,833
We knew.

896
00:34:30,834 --> 00:34:35,273
I don't look much like Park Bo Gum,

897
00:34:35,274 --> 00:34:37,713
so I didn't expect to get the part at all.

898
00:34:37,714 --> 00:34:40,483
When I got it, I was really happy,

899
00:34:40,484 --> 00:34:41,983
but I was very puzzled.

900
00:34:41,984 --> 00:34:43,913
Did you get to see him in real life?

901
00:34:43,914 --> 00:34:45,453
- Yes. - How was he?

902
00:34:45,454 --> 00:34:47,024
He has a very good personality.

903
00:34:47,254 --> 00:34:48,824
During the pre-reading,

904
00:34:49,084 --> 00:34:51,723
he was sitting across from me,

905
00:34:51,724 --> 00:34:53,254
and the table was really big.

906
00:34:53,624 --> 00:34:57,293
He was far away, but he came all the way to me...

907
00:34:57,294 --> 00:35:00,094
and asked me to take good care of Gwan Sik.

908
00:35:00,604 --> 00:35:03,463
It was my first time seeing an adult actor come over...

909
00:35:03,464 --> 00:35:06,873
to greet me himself first,

910
00:35:06,874 --> 00:35:08,473
so I was very grateful.

911
00:35:08,474 --> 00:35:10,773
Did you audition as well, Tae Yeon?

912
00:35:10,774 --> 00:35:13,013
I auditioned about four times,

913
00:35:13,014 --> 00:35:16,543
but on my third time,

914
00:35:16,544 --> 00:35:19,083
- I was in a car accident. - What?

915
00:35:19,084 --> 00:35:20,823
It was a big accident,

916
00:35:20,824 --> 00:35:22,183
but I told my mom...

917
00:35:22,184 --> 00:35:25,853
that I really wanted to do this,

918
00:35:25,854 --> 00:35:27,663
so we went to the audition.

919
00:35:27,664 --> 00:35:32,263
I've actually been a fan of IU since I was seven,

920
00:35:32,264 --> 00:35:35,933
and I really wanted to play her younger part.

921
00:35:35,934 --> 00:35:40,603
So I tried my best for the audition.

922
00:35:40,604 --> 00:35:42,673
I guess you got into the accident that day...

923
00:35:42,674 --> 00:35:44,514
because you were going to get the role.

924
00:35:45,714 --> 00:35:48,143
You were nominated for the Best Rookie Actress Award...

925
00:35:48,144 --> 00:35:50,314
at the Baeksang Arts Awards, right?

926
00:35:50,484 --> 00:35:51,584
That's right.

927
00:35:52,114 --> 00:35:54,483
That day, I came back home from the academy...

928
00:35:54,484 --> 00:35:56,283
- and found Mom crying so much. - Right.

929
00:35:56,284 --> 00:35:57,554
She was wailing.

930
00:35:57,754 --> 00:35:59,924
I asked her why she was crying, and she said,

931
00:36:00,254 --> 00:36:03,524
"You are nominated for Baeksang's Best Rookie Actress Award."

932
00:36:04,234 --> 00:36:06,463
I was really happy...

933
00:36:06,464 --> 00:36:07,804
because I really wanted to go there.

934
00:36:08,564 --> 00:36:11,273
I'm sure the other nominees are great,

935
00:36:11,274 --> 00:36:14,103
but I really hope you win the award.

936
00:36:14,104 --> 00:36:16,173
- I'm serious. - Ji Yul attended...

937
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:18,244
- the 2024 Baeksang Arts Awards. - She was there last year.

938
00:36:18,444 --> 00:36:19,874
- You attended the awards ceremony. - Really?

939
00:36:20,414 --> 00:36:23,684
(Ji Yul attended the Baeksang Arts Awards.)

940
00:36:24,054 --> 00:36:26,013
(She drew attention with her lovely look.)

941
00:36:26,014 --> 00:36:27,953
Did you tell her anything about the ceremony?

942
00:36:27,954 --> 00:36:30,084
"This is what Baeksang Arts Awards is like."

943
00:36:30,224 --> 00:36:31,323
Do you have any advice?

944
00:36:31,324 --> 00:36:33,454
I didn't tell her anything.

945
00:36:34,164 --> 00:36:35,863
But about the dress,

946
00:36:35,864 --> 00:36:38,734
you need to dress well at the Baeksang Arts Awards.

947
00:36:40,164 --> 00:36:42,764
- You need to dress well. - Right.

948
00:36:42,964 --> 00:36:47,874
That day, I wore a pink dress...

949
00:36:47,974 --> 00:36:50,274
because I looked good in pink.

950
00:36:50,614 --> 00:36:52,943
I think she would look good...

951
00:36:52,944 --> 00:36:55,944
in a black dress like she's wearing now.

952
00:36:56,484 --> 00:36:58,284
- She's very straightforward. - Right.

953
00:36:58,714 --> 00:37:01,683
- That's a senior's advice. - Black looks elegant and pretty.

954
00:37:01,684 --> 00:37:03,453
- Senior. - The color?

955
00:37:03,454 --> 00:37:05,724
- I need to go to the ceremony, - Yes.

956
00:37:05,854 --> 00:37:08,393
but I didn't know what to wear or do...

957
00:37:08,394 --> 00:37:10,933
because it was my first time going there.

958
00:37:10,934 --> 00:37:12,994
But IU called me...

959
00:37:13,164 --> 00:37:17,473
and said she would help me with the dress and makeup.

960
00:37:17,474 --> 00:37:18,673
IU did?

961
00:37:18,674 --> 00:37:20,873
- That's so nice. - So I went to try the dress,

962
00:37:20,874 --> 00:37:25,343
and she picked out the fabric and the gems.

963
00:37:25,344 --> 00:37:28,213
- I really wanted to thank her. - I feel envious.

964
00:37:28,214 --> 00:37:32,754
You never acted with IU on the same scene, right?

965
00:37:32,854 --> 00:37:34,983
We were never on the same scene,

966
00:37:34,984 --> 00:37:38,424
but we met at the filming site.

967
00:37:38,654 --> 00:37:41,864
She recognized me from afar and called my name.

968
00:37:42,024 --> 00:37:44,594
She helped me with the dress, invited me to her concert,

969
00:37:44,864 --> 00:37:46,894
and sent me a coffee truck...

970
00:37:47,234 --> 00:37:49,103
on the last day of filming.

971
00:37:49,104 --> 00:37:52,374
I was really happy and I was so touched.

972
00:37:52,774 --> 00:37:55,043
- And... - I heard Tae Yeon and Cheon Mu...

973
00:37:55,044 --> 00:37:56,544
prepared an awesome performance.

974
00:37:56,874 --> 00:37:58,273
- Really? - Yes.

975
00:37:58,274 --> 00:38:01,013
- Really? - We prepared a performance.

976
00:38:01,014 --> 00:38:02,843
We'd like to show it to you.

977
00:38:02,844 --> 00:38:04,253
- Okay. - I hope you like it.

978
00:38:04,254 --> 00:38:07,224
(I hope you like it.)

979
00:38:09,154 --> 00:38:10,923
One, two, three.

980
00:38:10,924 --> 00:38:12,554
- Give us the music. - Give us the music.

981
00:38:13,454 --> 00:38:16,924
("A Love Story of a Country Boy" by Ye Min)

982
00:38:17,394 --> 00:38:18,693
They're going to sing.

983
00:38:18,694 --> 00:38:21,234
(Swaying)

984
00:38:21,634 --> 00:38:23,204
An actor and an actress are going to sing.

985
00:38:23,534 --> 00:38:25,004
- That's amazing. - I know.

986
00:38:31,014 --> 00:38:37,654
(Kwan Sik, a boy of iron will, and Ae Soon, a literature lover)

987
00:38:37,914 --> 00:38:44,494
(A pure love story of the boy and the girl)

988
00:38:52,564 --> 00:38:53,934
She sings well.

989
00:40:34,204 --> 00:40:38,633
(A beautiful love story)

990
00:40:38,634 --> 00:40:43,973
(of a country boy)

991
00:40:43,974 --> 00:40:45,973
